<br>
When I started my magician, the idea of research appealed to me.  It's fun to think about the magician toiling in his spell research, working to improve himself.  When I actually started doing research, however, I quickly grew to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> despise</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> research. Spending days to collect components for a spell that I really need, only to lose the components on a failed combine (and then to do it again two days later!) is definitely i]not[/i] fun.<br>
<br>
Now when I have the research components for a spell that's very important to me, I find a higher level magician to do the combine for me.  This is a major hassle, but it's actually making me enjoy research again.<br>
<br>
In the process of seeking out higher level magicians to assist me in research, I've actually met quite a few outstanding players on my server.  These people have assisted me with their experience and wisdom, and I would have never met them if it weren't for spell research.  Spell research has also given me a reason to trek to places I'd not have travelled to otherwise, so that they can assist me.<br>
<br>
I'm continuing to train in research, however.  I think it'll be handy for doing the chain research I'll need for higher levels.<br>
<br>
One thing that amazes me, though, is how many 50+ magicians have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> zero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> research skill.  That just seems somehow wrong! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udionia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dionia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 7:39:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Spell research isn't all bad</span><hr size=1> You know, a lot of higher level magicians have zero research skill because they do the exact same thing you do. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
